# INTERPRETATION
# ============================================================
Main observed pattern:
  theta midpoint:
    θ(T)/π = n - 3/2
  gives a phase-centered guess for γ_n.
For known rows:
  The locator lands within a fraction of local average spacing.
  Hardy Z refinement then collapses the remaining error to the actual root.
For high rows:
  The asymptotic half-jump equation provides a remote locator scale.
  But high rows remain locator-only unless paired with:
    - trusted actual zero data,
    - Hardy Z bracket,
    - root refinement,
    - ξ centered-basin check,
    - finite certificate export.
Court boundary:
  This report supports:
    RH non-trivial zero locator pipeline.
  This report does NOT prove:
    RH,
    global no-off-ridge-zero,
    all non-trivial zeros lie on α=0,
    tail control,
    ghost exclusion,
    global bridge theorem.
Current correct statement:
  RH Non-Trivial Zeros Locator:
    no proof yet for RH.
  Finite evidence:
    useful.
  Global theorem:
    still open.
